y, Wales, United Kingdom","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales","of Llanafan Fawr,Buellt ctf,Breconshire,Wales":"Llanafan-fawr, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joyce","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Apparently from the Norman male name <i>Josce</i> (Middle English <i>Josse</i>), which in turn is from <i>Jodocus</i>, a Latinized form of a Breton name, <i>Iodoc</i>, meaning ‘lord’, borne by a 7th-century Breton saint. The name was in use in England among Breton followers of William the Conqueror. However, although this was fairly common as a male given name in the Middle Ages, it had virtually died out by the 14th century. There is evidence of its use as a girl's name from the 16th century onwards in parishes with strong Puritan links, which suggests that it may have been associated with the vocabulary word <i>joy</i>;  see  Joy .  It was strongly revived in the 19th century under the influence of popular fiction. It is borne by characters in Mrs  Henry Wood's  East Lynne (  1861 ) and  Edna Lyall's  In the Golden Days (  1885 ). Modern use may well have been influenced also by the common Irish surname derived from the medieval Norman male name.  See also  Joss ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ferch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferg","meanings":["From the vocabulary word denoting the plant (Old English <i>fearn</i>). Modern use of this word as a given name dates from the 19th century, when it is also recorded occasionally as a boy's name in the United States. In some instances the given name may be a transferred use of the surname derived in the medieval period from the vocabulary word."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Joyce ferch Maredudd was born in 1362, in Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom, her father, Maredudd \" Ddu\" ap Maredudd, was 20 and her mother, Mrs. Maredudd Ddu ap Maredudd, was 17. She had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Madog Crwm ap Trahaearn."},"et":{"1362–":"1362–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1360–1291":"1360–1291","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1384–Male":"1384–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1346–Female":"1346–Surnud","1346":"1346","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1384":"1384","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1291":"1291","about 1384":"umbes 1384","of, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom":"Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales","of Llanafan Fawr,Buellt ctf,Breconshire,Wales":"Llanafan-fawr, Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1362–":"1362–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1360–1291":"1360–1291","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","1384–Male":"1384–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1346–Female":"1346–Kuollut","1346":"1346","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1384":"1384","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1291":"1291","about 1384":"noin 1384","of, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom":"Anglesey, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Wales","of Llanafan Fawr,Buellt ctf,Breconshire,Wales":"Llanafan-fawr, Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1362–":"1362–Décédée","1362–Female":"1362–Décédée","1360–1291":"1360–1291","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","1384–Male":"1384–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1342–Male":"1342–Décédé","1346–Female":"1346–Décédée","1346":"1346","1342":"1342","1362":"1362","1384":"1384","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","1291":"1291","about 1384":"environ 1384","of, Anglesey, Wales, United Kingdom":"Anglesey, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Caernarfonshire, Wales":"Caernarfonshire, Galles","of Llanafan Fawr,Buellt ctf,Breconshire,Wales":"Llanafan-fawr, Breconshire, Pays